Cicero says: “The ‘ epulum ’ is so far funereal, that the show of gladiators is a part of the funeral, but the feast itself is for the honour of him who gives it.'’ Accord- ingly a man might be present at the show of gladiators in a dark dress, but he ought to have a light dress at the feast (Abrami).
